rComments: Nice person, fair grader, easy, fun class
Very nice teacher... baked muffins for us on the day of the final. Participation counts, um, she has a rule about not missing more than 6 classes.

She is a very hard grader, but has no insightful comment to back her up. None of the lectures come together with the readings either. Overall I thought the class was difficult but did not get much out of it.
Difficult grader but very willing to help. Participation points and other assignments can help boost your grade.
A fair grader. I thought she was a pretty easy grader. Shes pretty helpful if you go to her office hours.
Very willing to help. Grades papers a bit tough but makes up for it with other "effort" grades. If you work hard, you can get an A.
She is a tough grader, so you have to work hard.  She's really willing to help you, though.
Solid Teacher. Grades are not easy to earn but she is a fair grader. Recommended.
